# Gen Pulse — Docker build context exclusions.
#
# Rule of thumb: anything containing secrets, local runtime state, or
# pure dev tooling should NOT be baked into the container image. This
# file is enforced by both `docker build` and `gcloud builds submit`.
#
# Matters for Cloud Run because (a) smaller images cold-start faster,
# and (b) a leaked .env inside a Cloud Run image is permanently in
# Artifact Registry history — there's no quiet rollback.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Secrets — NEVER in an image.
# Cloud Run mounts these from Secret Manager at runtime instead.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Local runtime state — regenerated on every Cloud Run boot from
# the authoritative upstreams (Slack users.list, Workday CSV, etc).
# Shipping these would (a) bloat the image and (b) leak PII.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
data/
!data/workday-absences.example.csv
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
*.sqlite
*.sqlite-journal

# Tunnel state, QR codes, runtime logs — all ephemeral.
data/logs/
data/qr/
data/tunnel-state.json
logs/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Version control + IDE + OS noise.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
.git/
.github/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.vscode/
.idea/
.cursor/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Dev dependencies that npm ci --omit=dev would prune anyway,
# but excluding them here makes the build context smaller too.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-error.log
.npm/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Build-time scratch produced by the multi-stage Dockerfile —
# don't feed the output of a previous build back in.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
Dockerfile.bak
.docker-build-cache/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Markdown runbooks, admin-request templates, and dev scripts —
# useful in git, pointless in a Cloud Run container.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
*.md
scripts/demo-*.sh
scripts/tunnel-*.sh
scripts/activate-*.sh
scripts/set-*.sh
scripts/export-*.sh
scripts/probe-*.mjs
scripts/verify-*.sh
scripts/list-*.mjs
scripts/map-*.mjs
# Keep the GCP tooling available in-image only if something needs it
# at runtime — today nothing does, so exclude those too.
scripts/gcp-*.sh

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Test fixtures / snapshot data if we ever add them.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
test/
tests/
__snapshots__/
coverage/
.nyc_output/
